subject: Volleyball
lead_paragraph: The St. John’s women’s team dropped a five-game match against Southern California yesterday and was eliminated from the N.C.A.A. tournament in the Round of 16 in Gainesville, Fla.The defeat ended the best season in the 14-year history of the program. After losing the first two games, the 12th-seeded Red Storm (33-4) battled back behind the senior Hui Ping Huang, who had a match- and career-high 29 kills. Asia Kaczor led fifth-seeded U.S.C. (28-4) with 25 kills. U.S.C will next face Texas, which beat Florida in four games.
